# module: eng.io
# status: supported-builtins
# purpose: explicit source reads and generated output writes with reviewable hashes.
#
# Compiler/runtime built-ins:
#   read text path
#   read json path
#   read toml path
#   write text path, expression
#   write json path, expression
#   export summary to csv path { ... }
#
# Current contract:
#   read text/json/toml return raw UTF-8 text and record source-file hashes.
#   read json/toml also preserve structured parse status in
#   typed_payload.structured_reads[].
#   write/export operations are generated outputs and must appear in
#   output_manifest.json.
#   table-to-standard text artifact writing is exposed as
#   `write standard_text <table>` and recorded through eng.artifact.
#   structured json/toml promotion remains a future eng.config boundary.
#
# Diagnostics:
#   E-IO-JSON-PARSE: read json source is not valid JSON.
#   E-IO-TOML-PARSE: read toml source is not valid TOML.
#
# Pure .eng helpers:
#   none yet. Importable stdlib execution is planned; current behavior lives in
#   compiler/runtime built-ins.
